# When swapping a tiebreaker (removing one peer and adding another),
# del-peer must run AFTER connect, not before. Otherwise, if the connect fails
# (e.g. quorum constraints), the resource is left in a quorum-deadlocked state
# that cannot self-heal.
#
# The bug triggers when a Connected peer that needs no changes is processed
# by adjust_conn(C_CONNECTED), which resets the dependency chain (dcmd=NULL).
# This causes the subsequent del-peer to have no dependency on the new peer's
# connect, so it runs first at CFG_NET_PREP_DOWN before CFG_NET_CONNECT.
#
# Running state: peer0 (node-id 0) Connecting, peer2 (node-id 2) Connected
# Desired state: peer2 (node-id 2) keep, peer3 (node-id 3) new, peer0 removed
#
# Expected: new-peer/connect for peer3 BEFORE del-peer for peer0
$ FAKE_DRBDSETUP_SHOW=drbdsetup_show_tiebreaker_swap.txt drbdadm -c ./adjust_tiebreaker_swap.res adjust -d r0 2>/dev/null
drbdsetup new-peer r0 3 --_name=peer3
drbdsetup new-path r0 3 ipv4:10.36.50.13:7791 ipv4:10.36.50.11:7791
drbdsetup connect r0 3
drbdsetup wait-connect-connection r0 3 --wfc-timeout 1 --degr-wfc-timeout 1 --outdated-wfc-timeout 1
drbdsetup del-peer r0 0
